videos.headline: Akash Madhwal to Ashwin, out Caught by Tilak Varma!! MI needed that breakthrough and once again it is Madhwal who provides it! The skiddy nature of his bowling causes the downfall of Ashwin as he tries to play cross batted to this length ball on off stump. Gets a flying edge as he was slightly late on it. Lobs it behind backward point where Varma runs back to take a well judged catch. Ashwin c Tilak Varma b Akash Madhwal 16(16) [4s-1]

Akash Madhwal to Buttler, out Caught by Chawla!! Game on!! A short ball from Madhwal and Buttler couldn't resist himself. Top-edges the pull slightly and it goes straight down the throat of Chawla at fine leg. The fielder didn't have to move an inch. and makes no mistake. Buttler's poor start to the IPL continues, Mumbai are fighting back in this one! Buttler c Chawla b Akash Madhwal 13(16) [4s-2]

Akash Madhwal to Samson, out Bowled!! Chopped on! Madhwal has this happy knack of taking wickets and he's struck with his 2nd ball of the season - short and wide of off, Samson lazily threw his hands on the drive, the feet hardly moved and the thick inside edge clattered into his off-stump. MI keeping themselves in the hunt with timely wickets. Samson b Akash Madhwal 12(10) [4s-3]

Kwena Maphaka to Jaiswal, out Caught by Tim David!! Maiden IPL wicket for Maphaka - rush of blood and that has cost Jaiswal dear - on a good length and just outside off, it wasn't full enough for the drive, Jaiswal's feet didn't go anywhere as he threw his hands on the shot, chipped it uppishly and into the hands of David at cover. MI needed something to go their way and young Maphaka has given them a good start. Jaiswal c Tim David b Kwena Maphaka 10(6) [4s-2]

Nandre Burger to Tim David, out Caught by Boult!! It's not going MI's way tonight - David was refusing the singles, looks for the boundary option and holes out to deep backward square leg. Banged in short and he took it on with the pull, didn't bother to keep it down - Boult ran across to his right, reverse cup, and held on with ease. Tim David c Boult b Nandre Burger 17(24) [4s-1]

Chahal to Tilak Varma, out Caught by Ashwin!! Oh dear! This is going from bad to worse for the Mumbai Indians - Was thrown up full and wide of off, could've been a wide had Tilak let it go, but he's committed into playing it - he has to reach out to such an extent that he loses his balance on the cut, gets a thick top-edge that lobbed to the left of Ashwin at short third man, he moves across, dives and holds on. MI are in a hole now - can they even bat out the 20 overs? Tilak Varma c Ashwin b Chahal 32(29) [6s-2]

Avesh Khan to Chawla, out Caught by Hetmyer!! Mumbai Indians sink further! And how about that catch by Hetmyer! Was a short of a length delivery outside off and Chawla carved it towards backward point. Hetmyer dives to his right and completes a terrific catch. The ploy to send Chawla up the order hasn't worked for the hosts. Chawla c Hetmyer b Avesh Khan 3(6)

Chahal to Hardik Pandya, out Caught by (sub)Powell!! Just when a partnership was building, Chahal comes into the attack and breaks it. Nicely tossed up delivery on middle and leg, Hardik looks to go big and lofts it towards long-on and he miscues it altogether. Powell in the deep settles under the skier and completes a safe catch. MI have lost half their side with more than 10 overs remaining. Hardik Pandya c (sub)Powell b Chahal 34(21) [4s-6]

Boult to Naman Dhir, out Lbw!! Two wickets in two balls and Boult is on a hat-trick! On a length around middle and leg, the ball shapes back in and Naman Dhir gets rapped on the pads. Pitching in line, impact in line and it's clipping the top of leg stump. Mumbai Indians in trouble as they are 1/2. Naman Dhir lbw b Boult 0(1)

Boult to Rohit, out Caught by Samson!! Edged and taken! That's a fine catch by Samson! Short of a length outside off, Rohit has a poke at it and gets a thick outside edge. Samson dives to his right and takes a one handed catch. Sharma departs without troubling the scorers. A golden duck for him. Boult has troubled him in the past and he has gotten the better of Rohit again. Rohit c Samson b Boult 0(1)
